ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
-9=Missing; -5=Item/Instrument not collected; -2=Not collected at this time point
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

Location of Cast or Medical Prosthesis
Staff code number of person completing this form
What is your height? (Please give your best estimate.)
Average of two measured heights of subject in inches
Notes: Height of subject is measured two times and the measurements averaged.

ElementDescription: Average of two measured weights of subject in pounds
Notes: Weight of subject is measured two times and the measurements averaged.

ElementDescription: BMI calculated from averaged height and averaged weight
Notes: BMI of subject is calculated from the averaged height and averaged weight of subject.

ElementDescription: Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project (used for source IDs that change depending on timepoint/visit/etc.)

Notes: 1=Yes; 2=No; 3=Not applicable; 4=I prefer not to answer; -2=Not collected at this time point; -8=Unsure/Do not know; -9=Missing
